modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and manipulating STOG (Simple Text Object Grammar) data structures, including reading from and writing to byte streams. Operates on custom types such as `stog_node` and `stog_value`, enabling structured data representation. Used to serialize configuration objects and deserialize binary logs in network communication protocols.

Handles code rewriting by modifying attribute processing and tree structures. Operates on OCaml abstract syntax trees and attribute metadata. Used to block execution by altering how code is interpreted during transformation.
